2Cimgsize-45760.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fsports%2Fcricket%2Fnews%2Fglenn-maxwell-slams-fifth-t20i-hundred-to-equal-rohit-sharmas-record%2Farticleshow%2F107600996.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Glenn%20Maxwell%20slammed%20a%2050-ball%20century%2C%20his%20fifth%20in%20T20Is%2C%20as%20Australia%20raced%20to%20241-4%20in%20the%20second%20of%20three%20Twenty20%20internationals%20against%20the%20West%20Indies%20in%20Adelaide%20on%20Sunday.%20The%2035-year-old%20was%20in%20ominous%20touch%2C%20coming%20to%20the%20crease%20with%20the%20hosts%20on%2064-3%20in%20the%20seventh%20over%20and%20blasting%20eight%20sixes%20and%2012%20fours%20in%20a%20blistering%20knock%20of%20120%20not%20out%20from%2055%20balls.%20The%20hosts%20won%20the%20first%20match%20in%20Hobart%20by%2011%20runs%20on%20the%20back%20of%2070%20from%20veteran%20David%20Warner.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20SPORTS%20DESK%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Pak%20Ultra-Right%20Party%20Infamous%20For%20Anti-Blasphemy%20Protests%20Slips%20In%20Polls%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20leader%20of%20an%20ultra-right%20Pakistan%20party%20infamous%20for%20sometimes%20bloody%20anti-blasphemy%20agitation%20has%20vowed%20a%20comeback%20after%20its%20vote%20share%20evaporated%20in%20elections%20last%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBlasphemy%20is%20a%20charged%20topic%20in%20Muslim-majority%20Pakistan%20where%20the%20faintest%20whisper%20of%20a%20slight%20toward%20the%20Prophet%20Muhammad%20can%20embolden%20lynch%20mobs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESaad%20Hussain%20Rizvi's%20Tehreek-e-Labbaik%20Pakistan%20(TLP)%20party%20rode%20the%20issue%20to%20emerge%20as%20the%20largest%20Islamist%20force%20in%202018%20polls%2C%20but%20its%20prominence%20was%20all%20but%20eroded%20in%20last%20week's%20national%20and%20provincial%20elections.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnalysts%20say%20the%20death%20of%20Rizvi's%20charismatic%20father%2C%20who%20founded%20the%20party%2C%20and%20a%20loss%20of%20patronage%20from%20Pakistan's%20powerful%20generals%20cost%20them%20dearly.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpeaking%20to%20supporters%20in%20the%20centre%20of%20cultural%20capital%20Lahore%20on%20Saturday%2C%20Rizvi%20said%20the%20enemies%20of%20Islam%20had%20stopped%20his%20party.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20rigging%20has%20taken%20place%20because%20we%20speak%20about%20rights%2C%20and%20we%20talk%20about%20a%20faith%20that%20those%20with%20power%20in%20this%20world%20do%20not%20accept%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20AFP.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20asked%20if%20he%20could%20fill%20his%20father%20Khadim%20Hussain%20Rizvi's%20shoes%2C%20he%20responded%20matter-of-factly.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBringing%20people%20onto%20the%20streets%2C%20and%20bringing%20people%20out%20to%20vote%20was%20not%20a%20problem%20for%20TLP%20in%20the%20past%20and%20it%20is%20not%20a%20problem%20now.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20crowd%20of%202%2C000%20people%20there%20to%20hear%20him%20speak%20--%20though%20enthusiastic%20--%20was%20a%20far%20cry%20from%20the%20tens%20of%20thousands%20that%20used%20to%20hang%20on%20to%20his%20father's%20every%20word.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BKhadim%20Rizvi%20had%20the%20kind%20of%20leadership%20and%20charisma%20that%20his%20son%20does%20not%20have%2C%26quot%3B%20Arafat%20Mazhar%2C%20who%20works%20on%20blasphemy%20law%20reform%2C%20told%20AFP.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20added%20that%20religion%20had%20dropped%20down%20the%20pecking%20order%20in%20elections%20defined%20by%20%26quot%3Banti-establishment%20politics%26quot%3B%2C%20as%20Pakistan%20battles%20a%20massive%20economic%20crisis%20and%20an%20erosion%20of%20trust%20in%20institutions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%26quot%3BWe%20Have%20God%26quot%3B%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETLP%20has%20its%20ideological%20roots%20in%20Barelvi%20Islam%20--%20a%20mainstream%20sect%20traditionally%20seen%20as%20moderate%20but%20for%20which%20blasphemy%20is%20a%20red%20line.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20first%20began%20making%20waves%20in%202016%2C%20when%20protesting%20the%20execution%20of%20Mumtaz%20Qadri%2C%20a%20bodyguard%20who%20assassinated%20the%20governor%20of%20Punjab%20province%20over%20his%20stance%20on%20blasphemy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnalysts%20say%20its%20street%20power%20was%20tapped%20by%20the%20military%20a%20year%20later%20to%20reduce%20the%20voter%20base%20of%20Nawaz%20Sharif's%20centre-right%20party%2C%20which%20had%20fallen%20foul%20of%20the%20generals.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20were%20suspicions%20at%20the%20time%20that%20certain%20elements%20within%20intelligence%20agencies%20were%20encouraging%20them%20to%20destabilise%20the%20government%2C%26quot%3B%20public%20policy%20analyst%20Ahmed%20Bilal%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat%20element%20may%20no%20longer%20be%20there.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20party%20went%20rogue%20following%20its%20electoral%20success%2C%20orchestrating%20violent%20anti-Sweden%20and%20anti-France%20protests%20after%20incidents%20of%20Koran%20burning%20and%20satirical%20cartoons%20of%20the%20Prophet%20Mohammed%20in%20those%20countries.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESix%20years%20on%2C%20Sharif%20is%20back%20in%20favour%20and%20his%20successor%20Imran%20Khan%20in%20jail%20in%20the%20see-saw%20world%20of%20Pakistan%20politics%20--%20reducing%20TLP's%20utility.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFive%20years%20ago%20TLP%20bagged%20more%20than%20two%20million%20votes%20to%20become%20the%20fifth-largest%20party%20in%20the%20country%20--%20ahead%20of%20more%20established%20Islamist%20groups.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThursday's%20polls%20were%20less%20successful%20for%20all%20of%20Pakistan's%20religious%20parties%2C%20however%2C%20leading%20Rizvi%20to%20call%20on%20supporters%20to%20come%20out%20and%20protest%20on%20Saturday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20party%20had%20been%20tipped%20to%20gain%20more%20electoral%20seats%2C%20but%20Mazhar%20said%20its%20appeal